commit_message:
cliff pluging added

What is done:
* main cliff application setupped;
* setup.py modified in order to support cliff app structure;
* separate module for commands classes created;
* main app modified in order to keep backward compatibility with
  previous version of api;
* custom help action for main cliff app redefined, main parser for old
  prev code version modified to supply help message string in needed
  format;
* code independent global flags (e.g. --fuel-version, --debug) settuping
  removed from old parser, instead cliff definition of such options is
  used;
* debug mode for APIClient methods disabled because of difficulties in
  maintaining of arguments processing by prev code version parser;
* forming of optional args help for both parsers added;
* help command modified in order to support commads from previous
  version;
* commands for environment manipulation were implemented via cliff;
* unit tests for enviroment commands added;

